<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-533] A struct greater than certain size will cause an exception to be thrown and the data won&apos;t be written</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-533</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When writing a chunk of data greater than a certain size (like greater than a&lt;br/&gt;
couple hundred kilobytes), NSOutputStream can&apos;t write the data in one chunk.&lt;br/&gt;
The existing code detects this and throws an exception, so it is impossible&lt;br/&gt;
to send a struct greater than a certain size. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Attached is a patch which checks if all the data has been sent, if not it loops until finished.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
